  "presentation_notes": {
    "opening": "Let me walk you through our pricing model. It's designed to be completely risk-free for you.",
    "tier_by_tier": {
      "pilot": "[Point to left card] First, the pilot: 2 to 4 weeks, completely free. We'll work with 1 to 2 of your data sources, run in shadow mode for validation, give you a savings analysis report, do an architecture review. No commitment required. The idea is: prove value before paying.",
      "production": "[Point to middle card] Most customers move to production after the pilot. This is an annual contract with performance-based pricing. We charge X percent of your savings. [Pause] That's critical: We ONLY make money if you save money. If you save $2 million, we take a percentage. If you save zero, you pay zero. [Point to features] You get unlimited data sources, 24/7 support and monitoring, quarterly business reviews, custom policy development, and a success guarantee.",
      "enterprise": "[Point to right card] For enterprises‚Äîtypically Fortune 500s or those processing 200+ terabytes per month‚Äîwe offer custom pricing with volume discounts. Multi-year contracts. Everything in production, plus: dedicated customer success manager and technical account manager, custom SLAs and BAA, private deployment options, executive sponsorship. White-glove service."
    },
    "principles": "[Point to bottom section] Our pricing philosophy has three core principles. [Point to each] Aligned incentives: We make money when you save money. Transparent and predictable: You see exactly what you're saving in real-time dashboards. No surprise bills. No hidden fees. And fast ROI: Typical payback is 3 to 6 months. Most customers see positive ROI within the first year.",
    "objection_handling": {
      "specific_percentage": "If asked for the specific percentage: 'It depends on your total contract value and deployment complexity. Typically ranges from 15-30% of savings. We can model this exactly for your scenario.'",
      "comparison_to_per_gb": "If compared to per-GB pricing: 'The difference is: per-GB pricing punishes you for success. If you reduce 70% of your data, you pay us for 30%. We charge based on the SAVINGS, not the remaining volume. Our incentives are aligned.'",
      "what_if_no_savings": "If asked 'What if we don't hit 40% savings?': 'Then you don't pay. That's our guarantee. We've never had a customer not hit at least 40% reduction, but if it happened, you'd owe us nothing.'"
    },
    "transition": "Does this pricing model make sense? Do you have any questions about how it would work for your specific situation?",
    "when_to_use": "Show this slide only when pricing is explicitly asked about. Never lead with pricing.",
    "pacing": "Spend most time on the 'aligned incentives' concept. That's the unique selling point."
  },
